{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3ed-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"20915"},"text":"§ 20915.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Duration of registration requirement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3ee-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Full registration period","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A sex offender shall keep the registration current for the full registration period (excluding any time the sex offender is in custody or civilly committed) unless the offender is allowed a reduction under subsection (b). The full registration period is—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3ef-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 15 years, if the offender is a tier I sex offender;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f0-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 25 years, if the offender is a tier II sex offender; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f1-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the life of the offender, if the offender is a tier III sex offender.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f2-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reduced period for clean record","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f3-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Clean record","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The full registration period shall be reduced as described in paragraph (3) for a sex offender who maintains a clean record for the period described in paragraph (2) by—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f4-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" not being convicted of any offense for which imprisonment for more than 1 year may be imposed;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f5-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" not being convicted of any sex offense;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f6-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" successfully completing any periods of supervised release, probation, and parole; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f7-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" successfully completing of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002185"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002185"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. The word “of” probably should not appear."}],"tail":" an appropriate sex offender treatment program certified by a jurisdiction or by the Attorney General."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f8-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Period","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3f9-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a tier I sex offender, the period during which the clean record shall be maintained is 10 years; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3fa-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a tier III sex offender adjudicated delinquent for the offense which required registration in a sex registry under this subchapter, the period during which the clean record shall be maintained is 25 years.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3fb-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reduction","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3fc-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a tier I sex offender, the reduction is 5 years;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3fd-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s20915/b/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a tier III sex offender adjudicated delinquent, the reduction is from life to that period for which the clean record under paragraph (2) is maintained.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id4d34a3fe-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/248/tI/s115"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–248, title I, § 115","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-07-27"},"text":"July 27, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/595"},"text":"120 Stat. 595","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id4d34a3ff-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id4d34a400-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id4d34a401-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This subchapter, referred to in subsec. (b)(2)(B), was in the original “this title”, meaning title I of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/248"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–248","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-07-27"},"text":"July 27, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/590"},"text":"120 Stat. 590","children":[],"tail":", known as the Sex Offender Registration and Notification Act. For complete classification of title I to the Code, see Short Title of 2006 Act note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s10101"},"text":"section 10101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id4d34a402-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s16915"},"text":"section 16915 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
